435
00:24:59,100 --> 00:25:00,800
What's wrong, the wipers?

436
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:03,300
My tears, I can't...

437
00:25:06,000 --> 00:25:08,200
see the road.

438
00:25:09,200 --> 00:25:11,000
Never mind that.

439
00:25:11,400 --> 00:25:13,000
Very funny.

440
00:25:17,000 --> 00:25:18,400
Jiro!

441
00:25:20,400 --> 00:25:22,200
This is my first time.

442
00:25:23,700 --> 00:25:26,000
Know the taste of your tears?
Spicy? Sweet?

443
00:25:29,300 --> 00:25:30,700
Mild spicy.

444
00:25:36,700 --> 00:25:38,600
Sweet.

445
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:43,000
What's up?

446
00:25:44,000 --> 00:25:46,800
You've been circling
around the police station!

447
00:25:47,100 --> 00:25:48,500
Angry with us?

448
00:25:57,500 --> 00:26:00,400
Very nice morning.

449
00:26:00,500 --> 00:26:04,200
What's happening in world politics?

450
00:26:13,000 --> 00:26:15,200
No littering.

451
00:26:15,400 --> 00:26:18,000
Put them properly in the litter bin.

452
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:24,800
Yamatai people! Yamatai people!

453
00:26:31,400 --> 00:26:32,900
Hey you!

454
00:26:33,200 --> 00:26:34,700
Stop the car.

455
00:26:34,800 --> 00:26:36,000
Yes.

456
00:26:55,600 --> 00:26:57,500
- Thief!
- Thief!

457
00:26:57,900 --> 00:26:59,900
Newspaper thief! Milk thief!

458
00:27:00,300 --> 00:27:01,800
Now we got you!

459
00:27:01,900 --> 00:27:03,600
Somebody help!

460
00:27:05,200 --> 00:27:06,400
You!

461
00:27:10,900 --> 00:27:12,100
Jiro!

462
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:17,300
Bastards!

463
00:27:17,400 --> 00:27:19,600
- Those old delinquents!
- Right!

464
00:27:20,200 --> 00:27:22,000
You're a juvenile delinquent.

465
00:27:23,500 --> 00:27:25,300
You did quite a lot.

466
00:27:26,700 --> 00:27:29,500
Truancy, scribbling the walls
of headmaster's office.

467
00:27:29,600 --> 00:27:32,400
Destroying lab specimens,
beating up teachers.

468
00:27:32,500 --> 00:27:34,900
Extortion, shoplifting, rape.

469
00:27:35,300 --> 00:27:36,600
Attempted!

470
00:27:38,000 --> 00:27:39,500
Attempted.

471
00:27:39,900 --> 00:27:43,000
Stealing milk and newspaper
is a misunderstanding!

472
00:27:43,100 --> 00:27:44,500
Misunderstanding.

473
00:27:44,700 --> 00:27:45,900
Go.

474
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:49,000
Not until you tell me about
the Yamatai people.

475
00:27:49,300 --> 00:27:51,700
Those crazy old men?

476
00:27:55,700 --> 00:27:57,700
They live there!

477
00:27:58,500 --> 00:28:00,300
- Above a bomb.
- What?

478
00:28:00,800 --> 00:28:02,300
Exactly above it.

479
00:28:03,300 --> 00:28:06,900
"Near the war's end, there was
an anti-aircraft artillery there."

480
00:28:07,000 --> 00:28:10,200
"During the bombardment
on March 10, 1945,"

481
00:28:10,400 --> 00:28:13,000
"it was hit by several
250-ton bombs."

482
00:28:13,100 --> 00:28:15,000
"The artillery was destroyed,"

483
00:28:15,100 --> 00:28:17,900
"but there were at least
2 unexploded bombs."

484
00:28:18,100 --> 00:28:21,300
"The captain at that time,"

485
00:28:21,500 --> 00:28:24,700
"made a telephone report
on Apr 1, 1958."

486
00:28:25,300 --> 00:28:26,900
Sounds convincing.

487
00:28:28,100 --> 00:28:31,900
"The owner of the land
and house of that spot,"

488
00:28:32,000 --> 00:28:35,200
"Munechika Okonogi made
a similar report that day."

489
00:28:35,500 --> 00:28:37,500
- Munechika?
- Dad.

490
00:28:38,600 --> 00:28:40,400
He has such a house?

491
00:28:41,700 --> 00:28:42,900
Dad?

492
00:28:43,200 --> 00:28:44,700
- Yours?
- Yes.

493
00:28:45,400 --> 00:28:47,500
He's reported as missing.

494
00:28:48,300 --> 00:28:49,800
Don't mind that.

495
00:28:50,800 --> 00:28:53,900
This is some kind of sickness.

496
00:28:54,700 --> 00:28:56,800
- Sickness?
- He's been missing since...

497
00:28:56,900 --> 00:28:59,100
December 8.
It's his 3rd time.

498
00:28:59,300 --> 00:29:00,700
No, 4th.

499
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:02,700
He'll come home.

500
00:29:03,200 --> 00:29:04,900
- Is that true?
- No.

501
00:29:05,300 --> 00:29:06,500
5th.

502
00:29:07,000 --> 00:29:10,500
He probably won't
come home this time.

503
00:29:11,700 --> 00:29:13,600
He's been missing since December 8,

504
00:29:13,700 --> 00:29:16,700
they've been living there
since December 8,

505
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:19,700
they may have done
something crazy,

506
00:29:19,800 --> 00:29:23,300
they may have chopped
him up and buried him!

507
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:26,000
Stupid! Stupid!

508
00:29:26,200 --> 00:29:27,500
Shut up!

509
00:29:28,200 --> 00:29:30,400
The deceased...no..
his family is here!

510
00:29:30,500 --> 00:29:32,800
- He's not his real son!
- Stupid!

511
00:29:33,200 --> 00:29:34,900
Watch your mouth, idiot!

512
00:29:35,100 --> 00:29:36,900
Never mind.

513
00:29:37,700 --> 00:29:39,800
I'm adopted, Mr. Idiot.

514
00:29:40,600 --> 00:29:41,800
Mr. Idiot?

515
00:29:42,400 --> 00:29:45,600
But they're still
father and son, Mr. Idiot?

516
00:29:47,500 --> 00:29:50,000
- Watch your mouth!
- The unexploded bombs.

517
00:29:50,500 --> 00:29:53,500
Will they explode after 36 years?
That ever happened?

518
00:29:54,600 --> 00:29:55,900
Yes.

519
00:29:57,500 --> 00:29:59,600
I was in the naval air force.

520
00:30:00,700 --> 00:30:04,000
If the fuse is working,
it can explode.

521
00:30:04,600 --> 00:30:06,300
How? By impact?

522
00:30:07,700 --> 00:30:09,600
Say, a huge earthquake.

523
00:30:10,500 --> 00:30:11,600
Yes.

524
00:30:18,100 --> 00:30:21,200
It's calm today.

525
00:30:22,800 --> 00:30:25,500
Even after yesterday morning.

526
00:30:26,200 --> 00:30:28,800
An earthquake of that magnitude.

527
00:30:29,400 --> 00:30:32,000
What a relief.

528
00:30:33,300 --> 00:30:35,000
The earthquake yesterday...

529
00:30:35,200 --> 00:30:38,300
was 3 on seismic scale.
The paper says.

530
00:30:39,300 --> 00:30:41,000
While we're relieved...

531
00:30:41,300 --> 00:30:43,200
that our country is safe,

532
00:30:44,300 --> 00:30:45,700
remember...

533
00:30:46,400 --> 00:30:48,000
today is August 6.

534
00:30:49,500 --> 00:30:52,600
The day of the Hiroshima A-bomb.

535
00:30:55,500 --> 00:30:57,700
The family of Mail Minister...

536
00:30:59,000 --> 00:31:02,100
all died on that day.

537
00:31:03,990 --> 00:31:07,100
This is a sad day.

538
00:31:12,400 --> 00:31:13,700
Everybody.

539
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:15,900
A minute...

540
00:31:16,700 --> 00:31:18,900
of silence.

541
00:31:39,000 --> 00:31:41,500
Jiro, let's go home.

542
00:31:42,000 --> 00:31:44,100
Can't leave a patient alone.

543
00:31:44,600 --> 00:31:45,800
Sir.

544
00:31:46,500 --> 00:31:48,900
You look painful, what's wrong?

545
00:31:49,000 --> 00:31:52,000
If you have stomach ache, take a pill.
Or go to the toilet.

546
00:31:52,300 --> 00:31:53,500
Toilet.

547
00:31:54,100 --> 00:31:55,400
Shut up!

548
00:31:55,600 --> 00:31:57,000
Toilet, no...

549
00:31:57,900 --> 00:31:59,700
for going to the latrine,

550
00:31:59,900 --> 00:32:01,400
these 36 years...

551
00:32:01,600 --> 00:32:03,400
I live in pain!

552
00:32:03,600 --> 00:32:05,800
- Hemorrhoids?
- Shut up!

553
00:32:09,100 --> 00:32:11,100
At noon, around this day
36 years ago,

554
00:32:12,400 --> 00:32:14,600
when I was squatting in the latrine,

555
00:32:15,800 --> 00:32:17,800
a B29 bomber out of power,

556
00:32:17,900 --> 00:32:19,800
dropped a 250-ton bomb,

557
00:32:19,900 --> 00:32:22,800
the only one it had,
on our air field.

558
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:26,700
I rushed there,

559
00:32:27,400 --> 00:32:29,800
my 13 men were all
blown into pieces.

560
00:32:32,300 --> 00:32:33,600
I picked up...

561
00:32:34,500 --> 00:32:36,600
pieces of this size,

562
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:39,700
and put them in a bucket.

563
00:32:39,800 --> 00:32:41,300
This is the 8th time!

564
00:32:44,300 --> 00:32:45,500
Listen.

565
00:32:47,300 --> 00:32:48,500
Yes?

566
00:32:49,100 --> 00:32:51,700
They were all kids of your age.

567
00:32:54,400 --> 00:32:55,600
Your age?

568
00:32:56,200 --> 00:32:57,400
18.

