00:33:05,400 --> 00:33:06,600
17.

572
00:33:06,800 --> 00:33:08,100
You too.

573
00:33:09,900 --> 00:33:12,600
Mr. Osaku.
Please see the chief.

574
00:33:15,100 --> 00:33:16,300
Jiro!

575
00:33:18,700 --> 00:33:19,900
Damn!

576
00:33:20,500 --> 00:33:22,200
Bourgeois punk!

577
00:33:23,500 --> 00:33:25,300
I'm a proletarian.

578
00:33:25,500 --> 00:33:28,500
Someday I'll catch you
with this hand.

579
00:33:29,800 --> 00:33:32,000
What's so bourgeois about me?

580
00:33:32,100 --> 00:33:33,800
Where? Loan companies,

581
00:33:33,900 --> 00:33:37,000
supermarkets, restaurants, grills,
pachinkos, car rentals.

582
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:39,000
What?

583
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:40,700
Your family!

584
00:33:41,400 --> 00:33:43,400
- You don't know?
- I don't.

585
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:45,400
Do you?

586
00:33:46,100 --> 00:33:48,000
That girl last night,
she was paid...

587
00:33:48,100 --> 00:33:50,400
1 million to drop the charges.
Do you know?

588
00:33:50,600 --> 00:33:53,000
1 million? So little money?

589
00:33:54,000 --> 00:33:55,200
You know?

590
00:33:55,300 --> 00:33:57,700
But I haggled it to 50,000.

591
00:33:59,200 --> 00:34:00,700
Good girl.

592
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:03,900
But that 50,000 is still
a waste of money.

593
00:34:04,700 --> 00:34:07,800
Well then, I have scores to settle!

594
00:34:08,700 --> 00:34:10,500
Go home first.

595
00:34:10,800 --> 00:34:13,700
- Jiro!
- Stop your resistance!

596
00:34:14,200 --> 00:34:15,400
What?

597
00:34:15,500 --> 00:34:18,600
Do you know what car you have?

598
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:21,300
Tamiko drives a small car,

599
00:34:21,400 --> 00:34:23,500
- my brother a Benz!
- Oh that one!

600
00:34:23,700 --> 00:34:26,000
That that that...
that one!

601
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:32,200
Let me rephrase what you said.

602
00:34:32,900 --> 00:34:35,500
You want us to leave...

603
00:34:35,800 --> 00:34:39,500
this house that is built on our territory...

604
00:34:39,700 --> 00:34:42,000
and also this territory of ours,

605
00:34:42,300 --> 00:34:44,700
before August 15.

606
00:34:45,400 --> 00:34:46,900
Unconditionally.

607
00:34:47,500 --> 00:34:48,900
Right?

608
00:34:49,200 --> 00:34:50,400
Yes!

609
00:34:50,600 --> 00:34:52,600
Of course not.

610
00:34:53,200 --> 00:34:54,700
This is like...

611
00:34:55,900 --> 00:34:59,500
on July 26, 1945, 6 AM,
the declaration...

612
00:34:59,800 --> 00:35:03,500
demanding the
unconditional surrender of Japan,

613
00:35:03,700 --> 00:35:06,400
that is, the Potsdam Declaration!

614
00:35:07,000 --> 00:35:08,900
You won't offer us a new place.

615
00:35:09,200 --> 00:35:11,200
No compensation.

616
00:35:11,500 --> 00:35:13,000
Right, madam?

617
00:35:13,700 --> 00:35:17,500
Hey! You have never paid
a dime of rent!

618
00:35:18,000 --> 00:35:21,900
We never allowed you to
live here in the first place!

619
00:35:22,300 --> 00:35:24,200
You're wrong.

620
00:35:24,900 --> 00:35:26,600
Last year...

621
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:29,600
on December 8,

622
00:35:30,100 --> 00:35:33,900
your husband
Munechika Okonogi said...

623
00:35:34,500 --> 00:35:35,800
may I?

624
00:35:36,000 --> 00:35:41,100
"You may live here for free,
and forever."

625
00:35:41,200 --> 00:35:43,100
He made a promise.

626
00:35:43,500 --> 00:35:45,400
But that's not a written statement!

627
00:35:45,700 --> 00:35:48,200
The law doesn't recognize
verbal agreements.

628
00:35:48,400 --> 00:35:50,900
The law of Japan...

629
00:35:51,600 --> 00:35:54,500
doesn't apply to our country.

630
00:35:55,600 --> 00:35:58,400
You need the international law.

631
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:03,300
And my husband has been
missing since December 8!

632
00:36:04,500 --> 00:36:07,800
I don't know if he's dead or alive!

633
00:36:07,900 --> 00:36:09,100
Well...

634
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:11,800
Pardon me...

635
00:36:13,200 --> 00:36:18,000
do you know why
your husband ran away?

636
00:36:18,300 --> 00:36:19,500
No.

637
00:36:19,700 --> 00:36:23,800
That day, your husband
said this to us,

638
00:36:24,800 --> 00:36:27,300
"I saw the face of
my sleeping wife."

639
00:36:27,900 --> 00:36:30,900
"I got scared and jumped
out of the window!"

640
00:36:31,100 --> 00:36:32,500
Get it?

641
00:36:32,600 --> 00:36:33,900
What?

642
00:36:35,300 --> 00:36:38,700
This line is the border.

643
00:36:40,900 --> 00:36:42,800
Your passport please.

644
00:36:43,200 --> 00:36:45,300
- Passport?
- Yes.

645
00:36:45,800 --> 00:36:47,800
But you don't need a visa.

646
00:36:49,200 --> 00:36:50,700
I'm hungry!

647
00:36:51,400 --> 00:36:53,200
Oh yes!

648
00:36:53,500 --> 00:36:56,000
We haven't had lunch yet.

649
00:36:57,100 --> 00:36:59,200
How about chilled soba?

650
00:36:59,400 --> 00:37:01,000
Something light?

651
00:37:08,500 --> 00:37:10,600
I haven't had eels for so long.

652
00:37:11,100 --> 00:37:12,500
Thank you.

653
00:37:16,300 --> 00:37:18,900
City Councillor,
the thing you want to discuss...

654
00:37:20,700 --> 00:37:23,300
Your chief told me...

655
00:37:23,600 --> 00:37:25,700
you'll soon retire.

656
00:37:26,300 --> 00:37:27,500
Yes.

657
00:37:28,300 --> 00:37:30,300
August 15.

658
00:37:31,100 --> 00:37:33,600
Mr. Terao has lots of businesses.

659
00:37:33,800 --> 00:37:36,900
He wants your help
after you retired.

660
00:37:37,600 --> 00:37:39,200
Thank you.

661
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:42,900
I've been worrying about
my retirement.

662
00:37:43,700 --> 00:37:45,300
I'm counting on you.

663
00:37:45,600 --> 00:37:49,200
Less than 10 days before that.

664
00:37:49,900 --> 00:37:51,600
He has a favour to ask.

665
00:37:51,900 --> 00:37:53,600
And you'll work for him.

666
00:37:54,100 --> 00:37:58,300
So I arranged this meeting
for you two.

667
00:38:00,500 --> 00:38:02,000
What about?

668
00:38:03,100 --> 00:38:05,300
I'm looking for someone.

669
00:38:08,800 --> 00:38:11,000
But murder is my thing.

670
00:38:13,100 --> 00:38:14,600
If so,

671
00:38:15,100 --> 00:38:17,000
consider it as a murder case.

672
00:38:18,900 --> 00:38:20,600
Since December 8,

673
00:38:20,800 --> 00:38:22,900
no one knows
if he's dead or alive.

674
00:38:26,300 --> 00:38:28,300
December 8?

675
00:38:29,900 --> 00:38:31,200
Is he...

676
00:38:31,700 --> 00:38:33,400
Munechika Okonogi,

677
00:38:33,800 --> 00:38:35,200
age 57?

678
00:38:37,500 --> 00:38:39,400
- You know!
- Yes.

679
00:38:40,200 --> 00:38:44,000
His younger son Jiro
was here last night.

680
00:38:44,500 --> 00:38:46,000
Something...

681
00:38:46,800 --> 00:38:49,700
What's your relation
with the Okonogis?

682
00:38:49,800 --> 00:38:51,800
Relation...

683
00:38:52,200 --> 00:38:54,100
we have the same hometown.

684
00:38:55,200 --> 00:38:57,500
The Okonogis...

685
00:38:57,600 --> 00:39:00,800
are the descendants
of a noble family.

686
00:39:01,900 --> 00:39:05,600
That's the reason his family
is so tired from crying.

687
00:39:07,900 --> 00:39:10,300
We'll kick them in an elderly home!

688
00:39:11,300 --> 00:39:12,500
No.

689
00:39:12,700 --> 00:39:14,800
A madhouse is better.

690
00:39:15,300 --> 00:39:18,200
Even better...
the bomb blows them up!

691
00:39:20,900 --> 00:39:23,400
You saved 950,000 yen last night?

692
00:39:24,200 --> 00:39:25,600
Hey you!

693
00:39:27,400 --> 00:39:29,600
- Lend me that money.
- Where are you going?

694
00:39:29,700 --> 00:39:31,800
- Revenge.
- Jiro!

695
00:39:35,600 --> 00:39:38,300
Is the sauce too spicy?

696
00:39:38,500 --> 00:39:41,800
No. Spicy or sweet,

697
00:39:42,600 --> 00:39:45,500
it's good as ever.

698
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:48,400
Hey hey hey!

699
00:39:48,600 --> 00:39:51,800
The coming August 15,

700
00:39:52,000 --> 00:39:54,800
let's get on a coach,

701
00:39:55,000 --> 00:39:57,800
and go to a hot spring?

702
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:00,900
August 15? It's the Bon Festival!

703
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:06,000
You're Education Minister
and you don't know?

704
00:40:07,000 --> 00:40:09,600
- It's not the Bon!
- Easy, easy.

705
00:40:09,800 --> 00:40:11,600
- End of WW2.
- No.

706
00:40:11,900 --> 00:40:14,900
- The day we lost the war.
- What's the difference!

707
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:16,400
Great!

708
00:40:16,700 --> 00:40:19,400
Men and women in the
same pool, preferably.

709
00:40:19,700 --> 00:40:22,100
Hot spring, great!

710
00:40:22,500 --> 00:40:24,700
I forget there is such thing.

711
00:40:24,900 --> 00:40:26,500
Yes, Prime Minister?

712
00:40:26,600 --> 00:40:28,700
It sounds great...

713
00:40:30,100 --> 00:40:31,300
Oh...

714
00:40:31,800 --> 00:40:33,800
these 36 years,

715
00:40:34,400 --> 00:40:36,400
many things happened.

716
00:40:36,900 --> 00:40:39,500
I did many things.

717
00:40:40,400 --> 00:40:41,800
Me too.

718
00:40:44,500 --> 00:40:45,900
Many.

719
00:40:48,100 --> 00:40:51,000
I know, Finance Minister.

720
00:41:19,700 --> 00:41:21,200
Bastards!

721
00:41:22,800 --> 00:41:24,200
Excuse me.

722
00:41:27,700 --> 00:41:29,300
Nobody home?

723
00:42:09,700 --> 00:42:11,300
It's you!

724
00:42:11,400 --> 00:42:12,800
Attempted rape?

725
00:42:13,500 --> 00:42:15,500
You call that a greeting?

726
00:42:15,800 --> 00:42:18,400
- Why are you here?
- A courtesy call.

727
00:42:19,100 --> 00:42:20,500
To pay my respects.

728
00:42:20,800 --> 00:42:22,200
Respects or revenge?

729
00:42:22,500 --> 00:42:25,000
I took the blame for
the things you did.

730
00:42:27,000 --> 00:42:29,200
And I got it bad.

731
00:42:33,100 --> 00:42:35,100
Coming!

732
00:42:35,900 --> 00:42:38,400
Hello. Yamatai here.

733
00:42:38,500 --> 00:42:40,500
Yamatai?

734
00:42:40,600 --> 00:42:43,700
Is Jiro Okonogi at your place?

735
00:42:44,600 --> 00:42:47,200
- Jiro?
- It's me.

736
00:42:50,900 --> 00:42:52,500
Jiro?

737
00:42:53,500 --> 00:42:55,900
- I'm Tamiko.
- Tamiko.

738
00:42:56,800 --> 00:42:59,800
I'm busy. Don't call me.

739
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:01,400
Hang up.

740
00:43:01,700 --> 00:43:03,300
Yes, I know.

741
00:43:03,400 --> 00:43:05,600
Jiro Okonogi?

742
00:43:05,800 --> 00:43:08,200
You're one of them!

743
00:43:10,700 --> 00:43:12,800
Hello? Hello?

744
00:43:13,500 --> 00:43:14,600
Hello?

745
00:43:21,800 --> 00:43:23,600
We'll shoot the spy?

746
00:43:24,700 --> 00:43:26,900
Poor boy.

747
00:43:27,100 --> 00:43:29,200
Yes, but we must shoot him.

748
00:43:31,100 --> 00:43:33,600
I don't know about Japan,

749
00:43:33,800 --> 00:43:36,500
but 36 years ago,

750
00:43:37,300 --> 00:43:39,700
our country destroyed all...

751
00:43:39,800 --> 00:43:43,300
Type 38 rifles.

752
00:43:44,300 --> 00:43:45,800
Then use this.

753
00:43:46,500 --> 00:43:48,300
Hey! Don't!

754
00:43:49,600 --> 00:43:51,000
Don't?

755
00:43:53,500 --> 00:43:55,400
The night I became Army Minister,

756
00:43:56,200 --> 00:43:59,000
I fixed a gangster in Kabukicho
with one thrust.

757
00:43:59,800 --> 00:44:01,300
Army Minister,

758
00:44:01,400 --> 00:44:04,200
please destroy this weapon.

759
00:44:04,800 --> 00:44:08,600
The weapons of our country
are just stationery,

760
00:44:08,700 --> 00:44:10,900
or DIY carpentry tools,
such as...

761
00:44:11,800 --> 00:44:13,400
wooden pestle,

762
00:44:13,900 --> 00:44:16,600
hammer, radish grinder,
pencil sharpener,

763
00:44:16,900 --> 00:44:19,400
or braided rope.

764
00:44:19,700 --> 00:44:23,600
We only have that
kind of weapons.

765
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:25,800
Braided rope?

766
00:44:26,900 --> 00:44:28,500
We can hang him.

767
00:44:29,700 --> 00:44:31,400
We'll tie the rope at...

768
00:44:35,900 --> 00:44:37,500
What's wrong, Tamiko?

769
00:44:38,200 --> 00:44:39,500
Jiro...

770
00:44:39,600 --> 00:44:41,600
will be hanged in Yamatai!

771
00:44:41,800 --> 00:44:43,200
In Yamatai?

772
00:44:43,700 --> 00:44:45,000
Come on!

773
00:44:45,300 --> 00:44:47,800
But they're crazy, Ichiro!

774
00:44:48,000 --> 00:44:50,200
They may do anything!

775
00:45:08,200 --> 00:45:10,500
Are you joking?

776
00:45:11,200 --> 00:45:13,200
I'll go and see.

777
00:45:13,700 --> 00:45:15,100
Yes, bye.

778
00:45:15,600 --> 00:45:17,100
You're going there?

779
00:45:17,200 --> 00:45:18,800
Yes. What's wrong?

780
00:45:18,900 --> 00:45:20,400
If it explodes,

781
00:45:20,600 --> 00:45:23,400
all things will turn to dust
within 500 metres!

782
00:45:23,700 --> 00:45:25,900
You don't want to go,
then don't go!

783
00:45:26,200 --> 00:45:27,800
Go back to Traffic!

784
00:45:27,900 --> 00:45:30,000
"Beep beep!
10 km over! License please!"

785
00:45:30,700 --> 00:45:32,600
I'll go! May I?

786
00:45:33,000 --> 00:45:34,600
We'll go with pistols?

787
00:45:35,400 --> 00:45:37,500
Pistols? They're old people!

788
00:45:37,800 --> 00:45:41,400
Old people too.
Like the FBI...

789
00:45:42,800 --> 00:45:44,600
"Reach!" Just like that.

790
00:45:45,500 --> 00:45:47,000
I want to try that.

791
00:45:48,000 --> 00:45:50,000
You play mahjong too much?

792
00:45:50,200 --> 00:45:54,300
No.
"Reach for the sky your hands!"

793
00:45:54,800 --> 00:45:57,500
Telling them to raise their hands.

794
00:45:57,900 --> 00:46:00,000
Shut up! Go get the car,

795
00:46:00,100 --> 00:46:02,400
- The patrol car!
- No, idiot!

796
00:46:02,600 --> 00:46:04,400
You'll agitate them.

797
00:46:04,600 --> 00:46:06,400
Then my own car!

798
00:46:08,200 --> 00:46:10,800
Too slow! Can you go faster?

799
00:46:10,900 --> 00:46:12,900
Must be careful when riding together.

800
00:46:13,000 --> 00:46:15,600
- But this is illegal.
- Illegal?

801
00:46:18,700 --> 00:46:20,500
Let's take out this amount...

802
00:46:20,800 --> 00:46:22,500
of insurance for Jiro?

803
00:46:22,700 --> 00:46:25,900
Oh. With his father's insurance...

804
00:46:26,400 --> 00:46:27,900
- this.
- Yes.

805
00:46:28,700 --> 00:46:30,400
I've asked Iimuro...

806
00:46:30,500 --> 00:46:33,600
- to come here from Kansai.
- Good.

807
00:46:34,200 --> 00:46:36,400
<i>Dear friends,</i>

808
00:46:36,500 --> 00:46:40,800
<i>it's gymnastics time.</i>

809
00:46:41,700 --> 00:46:43,200
<i>As usual,</i>

810
00:46:43,400 --> 00:46:45,500
He's still playing cool!

811
00:46:47,000 --> 00:46:50,800
<i>after the gymnastics, put your...</i>

812
00:46:51,500 --> 00:46:56,500
<i>old newspaper, magazines
