Yes. An insurance salesman
came to your house,

848
00:49:29,700 --> 00:49:31,200
your mother said,

849
00:49:31,300 --> 00:49:34,200
"My husband already has
a 300 million yen policy."

850
00:49:34,500 --> 00:49:37,200
Is that true?

851
00:49:37,300 --> 00:49:39,200
Even if it is,

852
00:49:39,400 --> 00:49:42,500
this amount is just
an excuse to say no.

853
00:49:42,900 --> 00:49:45,100
That's not important. How's Jiro?

854
00:49:45,500 --> 00:49:46,700
Jiro?

855
00:49:47,000 --> 00:49:49,000
Oh. Labour Minister.

856
00:49:49,800 --> 00:49:51,500
He's fine.

857
00:49:53,000 --> 00:49:54,500
That's true.

858
00:49:58,700 --> 00:50:01,200
Let's go back to the insurance.

859
00:50:01,800 --> 00:50:04,900
Even if it's just half, 150 million...

860
00:50:05,100 --> 00:50:07,000
- "OK"
- Shut up!

861
00:50:08,000 --> 00:50:09,200
Hello.

862
00:50:09,300 --> 00:50:10,500
Hello?

863
00:50:19,900 --> 00:50:21,100
Stupid.

864
00:50:21,200 --> 00:50:23,800
- What's wrong?
- What's wrong?

865
00:50:23,900 --> 00:50:25,800
Thanks to you, he hanged up!

866
00:50:27,600 --> 00:50:29,400
But something is wrong.

867
00:50:32,500 --> 00:50:33,700
You!

868
00:50:34,000 --> 00:50:37,000
Check all the insurance
companies in Japan.

869
00:50:37,200 --> 00:50:40,500
No way! I have a date tonight.

870
00:50:40,700 --> 00:50:43,300
Going back?
"Beep beep! 10 km over!"

871
00:50:43,700 --> 00:50:45,300
No! I'll go!

872
00:50:56,200 --> 00:50:58,000
- Where to?
- Yamatai.

873
00:51:00,400 --> 00:51:01,800
Just kidding.

874
00:51:02,200 --> 00:51:05,300
The place closest to Yamatai.
Shinjuku, please.

875
00:51:12,200 --> 00:51:14,300
- Cheers.
- For a hard day.

876
00:51:15,000 --> 00:51:17,300
I didn't know there's
such insurance company.

877
00:51:17,500 --> 00:51:18,600
Yes.

878
00:51:18,700 --> 00:51:21,000
It's very bourgeois, sir.

879
00:51:22,500 --> 00:51:25,700
200 million for such a punk!

880
00:51:26,400 --> 00:51:28,600
200 million? Punk?

881
00:51:29,900 --> 00:51:31,800
The bomb may explode anytime.

882
00:51:33,000 --> 00:51:35,300
No, it isn't certain if it will explode.

883
00:51:35,400 --> 00:51:37,400
Still, they took out a 200 million...

884
00:51:38,300 --> 00:51:40,600
for him. Stupid!

885
00:51:41,200 --> 00:51:42,500
For Jiro?

886
00:51:43,300 --> 00:51:44,500
Yes.

887
00:51:44,600 --> 00:51:46,200
I found it out today.

888
00:51:46,400 --> 00:51:47,600
Stupid!

889
00:51:48,000 --> 00:51:50,600
- Give him some black coffee.
- Yes.

890
00:51:51,000 --> 00:51:52,300
Right now.

891
00:51:56,300 --> 00:51:58,000
I expected this.

892
00:51:58,900 --> 00:52:01,300
You've prepared it!

893
00:52:03,200 --> 00:52:05,700
My wife will never do such a thing.

894
00:52:06,400 --> 00:52:07,900
Forget it.

895
00:52:08,100 --> 00:52:09,500
About what?

896
00:52:09,700 --> 00:52:12,000
Why didn't you tell me earlier?
Idiot!

897
00:52:12,100 --> 00:52:16,600
For the whole day, I've been
looking for the father, not Jiro!

898
00:52:16,800 --> 00:52:18,800
OK. Drink your coffee.

899
00:52:19,000 --> 00:52:21,300
We'll start a surveillance
on Yamatai!

900
00:52:21,800 --> 00:52:24,200
But this is Saturday night!

901
00:52:24,400 --> 00:52:26,000
I don't mind.

902
00:52:28,300 --> 00:52:30,700
35 years. Never got late.
Never missed a day.

903
00:52:31,000 --> 00:52:32,800
My record is impeccable.

904
00:52:34,400 --> 00:52:35,900
I won't let Jiro...

905
00:52:36,100 --> 00:52:38,200
He's just an adopted son!

906
00:52:39,400 --> 00:52:41,500
His mom and brother are suspicious.

907
00:52:41,800 --> 00:52:43,800
I don't care.

908
00:52:44,100 --> 00:52:47,700
If this goes badly,
my retirement is ruined.

909
00:52:47,900 --> 00:52:49,300
And you...

910
00:52:49,400 --> 00:52:51,400
"Beep beep!
10 km over! License please!"

911
00:52:51,500 --> 00:52:53,000
You want that?

912
00:52:53,700 --> 00:52:55,000
Right?

913
00:52:55,800 --> 00:52:57,400
I don't mind.

914
00:53:01,300 --> 00:53:04,000
You're so good!

915
00:53:07,800 --> 00:53:09,300
Welcome!

916
00:53:19,400 --> 00:53:21,200
<i>The next day. August 7.</i>

917
00:53:22,100 --> 00:53:24,400
<i>Checking the catfish
in the morning...</i>

918
00:53:24,500 --> 00:53:26,100
<i>is one of my duties.</i>

919
00:53:28,000 --> 00:53:29,800
<i>It's quiet, but...</i>

920
00:53:30,400 --> 00:53:32,600
<i>the piano string-border is broken,</i>

921
00:53:33,000 --> 00:53:34,900
<i>intruders may come in.</i>

922
00:53:35,700 --> 00:53:37,000
<i>I noticed...</i>

923
00:53:46,500 --> 00:53:49,600
What are you writing,
Labour Minister?

924
00:53:51,800 --> 00:53:54,700
The chronicles of Yamatai.

925
00:53:55,500 --> 00:53:58,000
<i>Country of the Blooming 1980s.</i>

926
00:53:58,600 --> 00:54:00,400
That would be the book title.

927
00:54:00,500 --> 00:54:02,200
My bestseller.

928
00:54:02,600 --> 00:54:04,200
Great!

929
00:54:05,000 --> 00:54:07,000
The blooming 1980s.

930
00:54:07,100 --> 00:54:09,600
It's a micro country.

931
00:54:09,700 --> 00:54:12,000
It's a sunny country!

932
00:54:13,000 --> 00:54:15,300
No matter what,

933
00:54:15,500 --> 00:54:18,600
please leave a record
for posterity.

934
00:54:20,900 --> 00:54:22,400
Newspaper and milk.

935
00:54:24,900 --> 00:54:26,100
Yes!

936
00:54:27,300 --> 00:54:29,900
<i>Stealing newspaper and milk...</i>

937
00:54:30,400 --> 00:54:32,400
<i>is also the Labour Minister's work.</i>

938
00:54:32,800 --> 00:54:34,200
<i>A person here.</i>

939
00:54:34,400 --> 00:54:35,800
<i>A person there.</i>

940
00:54:36,200 --> 00:54:39,700
<i>I had a feeling
that it's a stakeout.</i>

941
00:54:41,300 --> 00:54:43,900
<i>At midday,
I went out and buy lunch.</i>

942
00:54:44,100 --> 00:54:47,800
<i>I went to a nearby supermarket
with Finance Minister.</i>

943
00:54:48,900 --> 00:54:51,800
<i>I felt that we're followed
by 2 or 3 men.</i>

944
00:54:52,900 --> 00:54:54,400
<i>I felt that strongly.</i>

945
00:54:55,900 --> 00:54:58,900
<i>Luckily, the Yamatai old men...</i>

946
00:54:59,000 --> 00:55:00,700
<i>didn't notice it.</i>

947
00:55:01,600 --> 00:55:03,800
<i>But who are these men?</i>

948
00:55:05,400 --> 00:55:08,300
<i>I think my brother is behind this.</i>

949
00:55:08,400 --> 00:55:11,500
<i>A plan to evict the Yamatai old men.</i>

950
00:55:12,700 --> 00:55:14,200
<i>But what about...</i>

951
00:55:15,000 --> 00:55:18,300
<i>that idiot cop?</i>

952
00:55:24,000 --> 00:55:26,800
I knew the police are working.

953
00:55:27,400 --> 00:55:28,900
I asked them to.

954
00:55:30,000 --> 00:55:31,100
You?

955
00:55:31,500 --> 00:55:33,000
Let's call it...

956
00:55:33,500 --> 00:55:36,800
diversion tactics. It's necessary.

957
00:55:37,500 --> 00:55:39,200
- Right, Ichiro?
- Yes.

958
00:55:41,000 --> 00:55:43,000
They're working, but...

959
00:55:43,100 --> 00:55:46,800
they're just a retiring cop
and a rubbish cop.

960
00:55:50,500 --> 00:55:52,200
Sir! Nothing unusual!

961
00:55:54,100 --> 00:55:55,300
Really?

962
00:55:55,700 --> 00:55:58,500
Somebody must be
about to take action.

963
00:55:58,700 --> 00:55:59,900
Who?

964
00:56:00,600 --> 00:56:01,900
Who?

965
00:56:02,600 --> 00:56:04,500
It's your job to find out!

966
00:56:05,800 --> 00:56:07,000
Like...

967
00:56:07,500 --> 00:56:10,000
someone aimless,
looking at the wrong way.

968
00:56:10,500 --> 00:56:13,500
There are 3 men with
the gaze of cops.

969
00:56:15,700 --> 00:56:18,000
What? And then?

970
00:56:18,800 --> 00:56:20,100
Nothing.

971
00:56:20,200 --> 00:56:21,800
You should follow them!

972
00:56:22,600 --> 00:56:24,100
Stop one of them.

973
00:56:24,300 --> 00:56:27,400
Make him talk!
You should know that, idiot!

974
00:56:28,200 --> 00:56:30,400
But my role is...

975
00:56:30,500 --> 00:56:32,700
find out who's going to kill Jiro.

976
00:56:32,800 --> 00:56:34,400
I'll get there, "Reach!"

977
00:56:34,500 --> 00:56:36,200
With my pistol, "Reach!"

978
00:56:38,400 --> 00:56:40,200
Go back to "Beep beep!".

979
00:56:40,900 --> 00:56:42,600
<i>The next day, August 8.</i>

980
00:56:44,000 --> 00:56:45,500
<i>Around 6 AM.</i>

981
00:56:46,000 --> 00:56:47,800
<i>The phone rang.</i>

982
00:56:48,900 --> 00:56:51,300
<i>Labour Minister is also the operator.</i>

983
00:56:57,600 --> 00:56:59,400
This is Yamatai.

984
00:57:00,200 --> 00:57:01,700
- Jiro?
- Yes.

985
00:57:02,000 --> 00:57:03,700
Labour Minister.

986
00:57:04,500 --> 00:57:06,700
Get me the Foreign Minister.

987
00:57:08,200 --> 00:57:10,000
Foreign Minister!

988
00:57:10,600 --> 00:57:12,000
Telephone!

989
00:57:13,100 --> 00:57:14,600
Foreign Minister!

990
00:57:18,500 --> 00:57:20,700
This is the Foreign Ministry.

991
00:57:23,800 --> 00:57:25,200
Compensation?

992
00:57:25,800 --> 00:57:27,200
1 million each?

993
00:57:27,300 --> 00:57:29,000
1 million?

994
00:57:30,500 --> 00:57:33,800
I'll call a cabinet meeting.

995
00:57:33,900 --> 00:57:35,200
Then...

996
00:57:36,700 --> 00:57:37,900
then...

997
00:57:38,100 --> 00:57:40,700
give you a reply...

998
00:57:40,900 --> 00:57:42,700
before 9 AM.

999
00:57:47,200 --> 00:57:50,000
<i>Labour Minister is also
the alarm clock.</i>

1000
00:57:51,200 --> 00:57:52,800
<i>Calling them in...</i>

1001
00:57:53,200 --> 00:57:55,300
<i>no, I'm calling them up.</i>

1002
00:57:55,500 --> 00:57:57,300
<i>But the Yamatai old men...</i>

1003
00:57:57,400 --> 00:57:58,800
<i>are sleepyheads.</i>

1004
00:57:58,900 --> 00:58:02,600
<i>If I leave them alone,
they'll sleep forever.</i>

1005
00:58:03,000 --> 00:58:04,300
Wake up!

1006
00:58:04,400 --> 00:58:06,000
Shut up!

1007
00:58:08,900 --> 00:58:11,000
<i>Waking them up is not enough.</i>

1008
00:58:11,900 --> 00:58:14,000
<i>They may sleep in the toilet.</i>

1009
00:58:15,700 --> 00:58:17,000
<i>7 AM.</i>

1010
00:58:18,400 --> 00:58:20,000
<i>Cabinet meeting began.</i>

1011
00:58:21,400 --> 00:58:24,300
<i>To start, Cabinet Secretary
told us his view.</i>

1012
00:58:26,400 --> 00:58:28,000
Since our independence,

1013
00:58:28,200 --> 00:58:30,400
we refuse to take Japan's...

1014
00:58:30,700 --> 00:58:33,000
pension or welfare.

1015
00:58:33,200 --> 00:58:35,800
So our financial situation is...

1016
00:58:36,100 --> 00:58:38,000
deteriorating day by day.

1017
00:58:38,400 --> 00:58:41,500
Regarding this situation,

1018
00:58:41,800 --> 00:58:44,600
I think we should discuss it.

1019
00:58:45,300 --> 00:58:46,500
Yes.

1020
00:58:46,800 --> 00:58:49,000
We've been living
on the bank savings...

1021
00:58:49,300 --> 00:58:52,000
and race winnings of
Finance Minister.

1022
00:58:52,100 --> 00:58:53,800
I'm really sorry.

1023
00:58:54,300 --> 00:58:57,200
Don't feel bad about it.

1024
00:58:57,400 --> 00:59:00,800
If it's for all of you,
I'd do anything.

1025
00:59:01,400 --> 00:59:03,800
Ever since the war, I've been...

1026
00:59:03,900 --> 00:59:06,700
We all know that,
Finance Minister.

1027
00:59:07,800 --> 00:59:09,000
Yes.

1028
00:59:09,700 --> 00:59:13,000
There are very few jobs lately.

1029
00:59:13,600 --> 00:59:15,800
They all want young people.

1030
00:59:16,100 --> 00:59:18,000
Jobs for the old...

1031
00:59:18,400 --> 00:59:20,200
cleaning public toilets,

1032
00:59:20,300 --> 00:59:22,100
signal giver at construction.

1033
00:59:22,600 --> 00:59:25,700
Processing corpses
for anatomy classes.

1034
00:59:26,100 --> 00:59:27,700
I can't do that.

1035
00:59:27,900 --> 00:59:30,700
I tried it once, and
I felt like a corpse myself.

1036
00:59:31,200 --> 00:59:32,500
If so,

1037
00:59:33,800 --> 00:59:36,100
any work other than killing?

1038
00:59:36,200 --> 00:59:38,400
I can work for you.

1039
00:59:42,600 --> 00:59:44,800
You want to run away?

1040
00:59:45,300 --> 00:59:48,000
I can run away anytime!

1041
00:59:48,100 --> 00:59:49,700
You got me angry!

1042
00:59:49,900 --> 00:59:51,200
What the...

1043
00:59:51,400 --> 00:59:53,900
- What's wrong with you?
- Easy, easy.

1044
00:59:54,100 --> 00:59:55,900
Our country is in trouble,

1045
00:59:56,000 --> 00:59:58,500
no infighting please.

1046
00:59:59,000 --> 01:00:00,300
Right.

1047
01:00:00,500 --> 01:00:02,700
Please don't do the things...

1048
01:00:02,900 --> 01:00:04,700
they do in the Japanese Diet.

1049
01:00:08,000 --> 01:00:10,500
Whatever. Remember
I can run away anytime.

1050
01:00:11,500 --> 01:00:13,000
I need some fresh air.

1051
01:00:14,400 --> 01:00:17,100
Please continue, Cabinet Secretary.

1052
01:00:20,200 --> 01:00:21,200
I...

1053
01:00:22,100 --> 01:00:23,400
So,

1054
01:00:24,000 --> 01:00:27,700
there's no other choice other
than taking the 1 million?

1055
01:00:28,600 --> 01:00:29,800
Right.

1056
01:00:30,700 --> 01:00:34,000
If we take it,
it's the end of our country.

1057
01:00:34,200 --> 01:00:36,900
We'll be vagabonds again.

1058
01:00:37,500 --> 01:00:39,600
Don't forget this.

1059
01:00:40,000 --> 01:00:41,300
Also,

1060
01:00:41,700 --> 01:00:45,200
30 million yen is the
minimum for retirement.

1061
01:00:45,600 --> 01:00:47,000
It's common sense.

1062
01:00:47,100 --> 01:00:49,600
1 million? Is that right?

1063
01:00:50,200 --> 01:00:51,600
Forget it!

1064
01:00:52,200 --> 01:00:53,400
Yes.

1065
01:00:53,500 --> 01:00:55,300
Ignore it.

1066
01:00:55,500 --> 01:00:58,800
By the way, it's hot last night.

1067
01:00:59,100 --> 01:01:01,000
We need an air-con.

1068
01:01:01,600 --> 01:01:03,000
But,

1069
01:01:03,100 --> 01:01:06,200
I have the position of
Foreign Minister.

1070
01:01:06,600 --> 01:01:09,700
If we don't give them a reply,

1071
01:01:10,200 --> 01:01:12,600
it's a breach of international trust.

1072
01:01:12,700 --> 01:01:13,900
OK.

1073
01:01:14,300 --> 01:01:16,600
The reply is no.

1074
01:01:18,300 --> 01:01:21,500
Do you agree?
Please raise your hands.

1075
01:01:22,000 --> 01:01:23,300
Well...

1076
01:01:23,500 --> 01:01:25,000
When I woke up,

1077
01:01:25,300 --> 01:01:27,900
I had "50 shoulder".
I can't raise...

1078
01:01:29,200 --> 01:01:31,800
You're 69. Why 50 shoulder?

1079
01:01:32,500 --> 01:01:33,800
Young man.

1080
01:01:34,200 --> 01:01:36,600
Just show us your palm.

1081
01:01:44,500 --> 01:01:45,900
<i>Oh yes.</i>

1082
01:01:46,800 --> 01:01:49,300
<i>I can run away if I want to.</i>

1083
01:01:50,800 --> 01:01:52,600
<i>What's wrong with me?</i>

1084
01:01:54,000 --> 01:01:56,300
How about you, Labour Minister?

1085
01:01:56,600 --> 01:01:58,100
For? Against?

1086
01:01:58,300 --> 01:02:00,600
Raise your hand. No?

1087
01:02:02,900 --> 01:02:05,400
<i>Foreign Minister replied "No".</i>

1088
01:02:05,600 --> 01:02:07,000
<i>My brother...</i>

1089
01:02:07,200 --> 01:02:10,500
<i>no, the Okonogis responded
with "Ignore".</i>

1090
01:02:11,000 --> 01:02:13,600
<i>That is, hanging up.</i>

1091
01:02:14,000 --> 01:02:17,000
<i>This also means "Warning".</i>

1092
01:02:19,700 --> 01:02:21,100
<i>August 10.</i>

1093
01:02:22,400 --> 01:02:24,100
<i>Our phone line was cut.</i>

1094
01:02:25,500 --> 01:02:28,000
<i>That noon, Finance Minister
wanted to tell us...</i>

1095
01:02:28,100 --> 01:02:30,000
<i>that her bus ticket was nicked,</i>

1096
01:02:30,100 --> 01:02:32,200
<i>so she'd come home late.</i>

1097
01:02:32,600 --> 01:02:35,800
<i>She couldn't get through.
So we knew.</i>

1098
01:02:40,000 --> 01:02:41,500
<i>The scary part...</i>

1099
01:02:42,000 --> 01:02:43,500
<i>was that she...</i>

1100
01:02:43,600 --> 01:02:46,400
<i>stole someone's wallet
and came home in triumph.</i>

1101
01:02:49,800 --> 01:02:52,100
<i>Gymnastics time.
Today is no exception.</i>

1102
01:02:58,000 --> 01:03:00,000
I'll sneak in your home tonight.

1103
01:03:00,500 --> 01:03:02,200
To kill my brother?

1104
01:03:03,100 --> 01:03:04,600
No more killing.

1105
01:03:05,500 --> 01:03:07,900
To steal something?

1106
01:03:08,000 --> 01:03:09,200
Fool.

1107
01:03:09,400 --> 01:03:12,300
- Reconnaissance.
- Reconnaissance?

1108
01:03:13,500 --> 01:03:15,000
Show me around.

1109
01:03:15,200 --> 01:03:16,600
If I say...

1110
01:03:16,900 --> 01:03:18,600
- What?
- no...

1111
01:03:20,000 --> 01:03:21,200
Kill you!

1112
01:03:29,400 --> 01:03:30,600
Damn!

1113
01:03:31,800 --> 01:03:33,000
Useless!

1114
01:03:33,400 --> 01:03:36,000
Please! Let me try again!

1115
01:03:36,800 --> 01:03:38,500
You may.

